defs.name: UnsupportedType

Indicates that a Rust type was requested to be serialized but it was not
 supported.

defs.name: KeyNotString
defs.docs:
The key of all TOML maps must be strings, but serialization was
 attempted where the key of a map was not a string.

defs.name: KeyNewline
defs.docs: An error that we never omit but keep for backwards compatibility

defs.name: ArrayMixedType
defs.docs:
Arrays in TOML must have a homogenous type, but a heterogeneous array
 was emitted.

defs.name: ValueAfterTable
defs.docs:
All values in a TOML table must be emitted before further tables are
 emitted. If a value is emitted *after* a table then this error is
 generated.

defs.name: DateInvalid
defs.docs: A serialized date was invalid.

defs.name: NumberInvalid
defs.docs: A serialized number was invalid.

defs.name: UnsupportedNone
defs.docs: None was attempted to be serialized, but it's not supported.

defs.docs:
A custom error which could be generated when serializing a particular
